class Solution:
    def isUnivalTree(self, root: Optional[TreeNode]) -> bool:
        if not root:
            return True

        def is_unival(node, value):
            if not node:
                return True
            if node.val != value:
                return False
            return is_unival(node.left, value) and is_unival(node.right, value)

        return is_unival(root, root.val)
```

This solution defines a helper function `is_unival` that recursively checks if all nodes in the subtree rooted at `node` have the same value as the `value` parameter. The main function `isUnivalTree` initiates this check with the root's value.
